[{"id":"VR876948","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">How does the voltmeter reading immediately <span class=\"formatted_text text_decoration:underline\">after</span> the switch is closed compare to the reading before the switch is closed?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR876948_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A resistor of resistance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"R\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mi>R</mi></mstyle></math></span></span> and an uncharged capacitor of capacitance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"C\" overflow=\"scroll\"> <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"> <mi>C</mi> </mstyle> </math></span></span> are connected in a circuit with a nonideal battery that has <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"e m f\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"e m f\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>emf</mtext></math></span></span> <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"script uppercase E\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"script uppercase E\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mi>∆ê</mi></mstyle></math></span></span> and internal resistance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"r\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"r\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mi>r</mi></mstyle></math></span></span>. The circuit also contains switch <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"S\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"S\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>S</mtext></math></span></span> and an ideal voltmeter, as shown. The reading of the voltmeter is noted with the switch in the open position, and the switch is then closed.</p>\n\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a rectangular circuit diagram with a voltmeter, a battery, two resistors, a capacitor, and an open switch. The circuit has three vertical branches and two horizontal branches. The left vertical branch has a voltmeter. From bottom to top, the inner vertical branch has a battery with e m f script uppercase E and a resistor with resistance lowercase r. The battery and the resistor with resistance lowercase r are enclosed in a dashed rectangle. The right vertical branch has a resistor with resistance uppercase R. The bottom horizontal branch has a capacitor with capacitance C between the inner vertical branch and the right vertical branch. The top horizontal branch has an open switch labeled S between the inner vertical branch and the right vertical branch.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR876948.g02.svg\" /></div>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">It is higher.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">It is lower.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">It is the same and is zero.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">It is the same and is not zero.</p>"],"answer":1}]